The output appears to be a valid ROC curve. The first array represents false positive rates (FPR) at various threshold values, and the second array represents true positive rates (TPR) at those same threshold values.

It is worth noting that the output appears to be truncated, meaning some values may be missing. In particular, it is unclear what the TPR and FPR are at a threshold of 0.5, which is a commonly used threshold value. Additionally, it is unclear how many data points are being used to generate this curve, and whether there are any outliers or other unusual features that could affect its interpretation.
